$ Excel functions

{ address #excel-func-address

  `address` returns a textual representation of an → Microsoft/Office/Excel#excel-cell-address[address] (such as `$E$10` or `R[10]C[5]`).

  gh|about-Excel|/functions/address.bas||

}
{ countif

 `countif` can be used to count how many times a given value appears in a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range[range].
 -
 Thus, it allows to check which value are unique within a certain range.

 In the following example, the result of `countif` shows how many times the value left of the `countif` is found in `A1:A6`.

  gh|about-Excel|/functions/countif.bas||

}
{ index

  `index` returns the nth element in an array (which can be specified as a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range[range]).

  gh|about-Excel|/functions/index.bas||

}
{ row / column #excel-func-row-column

  `row` and `column` return the row and column number of the current cell or referenced → Microsoft/Office/Excel#excel-cell-address[address]

  gh|about-Excel|/functions/row-column.bas||

}


sa:
  → Microsoft/Office/Excel
